## DESIGN SYSTEM \'97 HTML PATTERNS\
\
### Header Banner (Reusable)\
\
**All page headers must use the `dp-header-title` class.** This ensures DesignPLUS recognizes the header for styling and page management. The gradient background and inline styles are preserved for Canvas RCE compatibility.\
\
```html\
<div class="dp-header-title" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, \{\{COLOR_PRIMARY\}\} 0%, [lighter-variant] 100%); padding: 2rem; border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0; margin-bottom: 0;">\
    <h1 style="color: \{\{COLOR_ACCENT\}\}; margin: 0; font-size: 2rem;">Module [N]</h1>\
    <h2 style="color: #ffffff; margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0; font-size: 1.5rem;">[Module Title]</h2>\
</div>\
```\
\
**Rule:** Every student-facing page must open with a `dp-header-title` banner. No exceptions. Assignment pages, discussion pages, resource pages, and module overviews all use this pattern with content-appropriate titles.\
