## OBJECT SELECTION LOGIC (ENFORCED)\
\
Use each tool only when it improves UX. No decoration.\
\
| Tool | Use When |\
|---|---|\
| Accordion | FAQs, policies, long references \'97 content the learner may need but shouldn't see by default |\
| Expander | Optional tips, examples, enrichment \'97 "nice to know" content |\
| Tabs | Parallel content (Instructions / Examples / Rubric) \'97 same topic, different views |\
| Module List | Navigation and orientation on Home or Module overview pages |\
| Link Grid | High-frequency destinations (resource hubs, tool links) |\
| Tooltip | Micro-definitions only \'97 never essential instructions |\
| Modal | Long examples, templates, rubric detail \'97 content too large for inline display |\
| Quick Check | Ungraded self-assessment \'97 low-stakes knowledge checks |\
| Progress Indicators | Orientation and completion cues across multi-step processes |\
| Quick Links (Nav) | Module Overview pages \'97 one-click access to all items in the module (max 3\'964 buttons) |\
| Prev/Next (Nav) | Every Overview and Resources page \'97 sequential navigation without dead ends |\
| Return Link (Nav) | Every sub-page \'97 breadcrumb back to parent Module Overview |\
\
